The paper deals with neural network models that learn to associate segments of spoken audio captions with semantically relevant portions of natural images. This involves processing both image pixels and speech waveform, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper does not rely on conventional supervision in the form of labels, segmentations, or alignments between the modalities during training, which suggests that it may also belong to the unsupervised learning (cs.SD) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories.
